cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on investigating the benefits of sharing infrastructure and spectrum among two cellular operators to address the data capacity crisis in cellular networks. This falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses stochastic geometry to develop a multi-cell analytical model to identify the performance gain under different sharing strategies. This involves the use of information theory concepts and techniques. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the benefits of cooperation and sharing among cellular operators, which can be seen as a social network of sorts. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper uses a multi-cell OFDMA system to conduct simulations, which involves the transmission of multimedia data. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses the benefits of sharing infrastructure and spectrum among cellular operators, which can be seen as a form of distributed computing.
